rComments: His course is very interesting and not extremely hard. He is himself a really nice and approachable guy, who is always willing to help and clarify the complicated concepts. Midterm and term paper may be a little bit tough, but final is very straightforward. Besides, he posts the past tests with solutions on the course website.

Truly engaging professor. The material is sometimes too mathematical, but I really liked the examples used in class and the discussions. Fair exams with lots of pars examples. Highly recommend the course.

Great prof, lectures were a little dry but he tried to make it interesting. Midterms were fair wrt questions but he graded a little too difficult. Also be sure to check over your midterms when he hands them back, he made a few errors when marking both. Final exam was brutal - pretty sure he scaled grades up at the end of the course. Recommended!

His lectures aren't too boring or difficult to follow, I didnt really study too much for this course but review of problem sets is need to be comfortable with the material. I reccommend the course as well as the professor.  Test material is predictable but requires sound knowlegde to do well, however this is not too hard with moderate studying.
